    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-14T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="930"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-14T16:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">December 14, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>I have explained to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">Spring
                        Rice</persName> that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HGM1">Hitchcock</persName>
                    did not consult the President or State Department in regard to his resolution.
                    Though from Nebraska he is not personally friendly to me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
